parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of the vehicle's speed, engine temperature, fuel level, and other critical information, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The speedometer
temperature gauge
fuel gauge
and other gauges on the instrument cluster malfunction or stop working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start
the interior lights flash on and off
and the ignition switch sensor malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various components to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The interior lights malfunction
the vehicle's electrical system fails
and the ignition switch sensor malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls while driving
and the vehicle loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter control cable can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not move when shifting into gear
the transmission does not engage
the vehicle is stuck in one gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic clutch line can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Window Motor and Regulator Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power window motor and regulator can cause the windows to malfunction, leading to safety risks, such as obstructed vision, and inconvenience to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The windows may not open or close properly
stick
or move slowly; the motor may make a loud noise or produce rust; the window may shatter or fall off track; the defroster may not work
causing dangerous driving conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the defroster can cause reduced visibility, leading to dangerous driving conditions, especially during winter weather.
symptoms: The defroster may not blow air onto the windshield
or may only blow air onto the dashboard; the windshield may not clear properly
causing reduced visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Windshield Wiper Motor and Circuit Board Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the windshield wiper motor and circuit board can cause reduced visibility, leading to dangerous driving conditions, especially during inclement weather.
symptoms: The windshield wipers may not work properly
or may work intermittently; the wiper motor may fail
causing the wipers to stop working altogether.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the rear view mirror can cause reduced visibility, leading to dangerous driving conditions.
symptoms: The rear view mirror may shake uncontrollably.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Trunk Lid and Rear Window Seal Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the trunk lid and rear window seal can cause water to leak into the trunk and rear seat, leading to damage and inconvenience.
symptoms: The trunk lid may have broken bolts
and the rear window seal may not be properly installed
causing water to leak into the trunk and rear seat.
